snippet.textDisplay: Bamfords hold up play this, Bamfords hold up play that. This excuse to play a so-called striker is wearing as thin as the Leeds squad. The Jan transfer window business will come back to bite us. Bamfords header looked more like a backpass and just about sums up his lack of potency in front of goal. With a "not fit and ready" Augustin out with a soft injury who can Leeds fall back on to deliver the goods with all this pressing play and hard work? The striker issue should have been rectified in January, irrespective of price and wages. Leeds need to get out of this cursed League and recently the games are producing a one-goal difference. Yes it's 3 points, yes Leeds are 5 points clear, but it could have been a different story if Borough didn't hit the post. West Brom have Robson-Kanu, Fulham has Mitrovic, Forest have Grabban and Leeds have Bamford. The latter does not even compare in quality and finishing prowess. I'm beginning to believe it's not just the Championship that is Leeds curse, I believe Bamford has put some Voodoo on the pitch as well. Anyone know where Bielsa's family is? I'm sure Bamford has them at ransom in a shipping container somewhere !!

snippet.textDisplay: I love Bamford's work rate and heart, and all the other good things he does for the team, but I'm tired of all this talk of him being unlucky: ultimately, a professional makes his own luck, and must be accountable for his entire body of work.  He is a striker who has the highest miss per chances taken rate in the league--by a wide margin.  On a team that averages a third more shots per game than the league average. He should already be sitting on 30 goals. Forget Kiko's erratic plays - if Bam did his job just to a statistically satisfactory level, we'd be top of the league and 15 points clear right now - easily.  The problem right now is that his confidence is so low, he needs to sit for a few matches, but with JKA hurt and not up to Bielsa fitness yet, and Roberts fragile as a glass factory, we are forced to keep running him out there. Thankfully, a new hero steps up each match to get us points. I still think Bam has a scoring streak left in him this season, which would be massive for LUFC---but he needs a break. Physically, mentally, he just can't buy a goal. MOT
